narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Honestly, even though I had fun (by not taking it too seriously), I wouldn't recommend it. Even though I wasn't taking it too seriously, I really felt frustrated by the lack of depth. You really lose a chance to appreciate the language/culture moving as quickly as this course does; basically, it felt rushed.
German 120 is a good continuation of 110, and runs in exactly the same format. Florian is a great professor - take it with him if you can!
Take it! German is a lot of fun to learn.
German L2 is a fun course that's not too heavy in workload. The final project is really fun!
